            "source": "PR NewsWire",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "In Hong Kong on March 7, 2025, it was announced that the Global Mobile Award (GLOMO) was presented to the 5G UAV medical delivery network solution at the 2025 Mobile World Congress (MWC25). This innovative solution was developed collaboratively by China Telecom, Hangzhou Antwork Network Technology, and Zhejiang University. The award recognizes the impact of their cutting-edge technology in the mobile industry. The solution aims to enhance medical delivery services using unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and 5G technology. This achievement highlights the potential of this network solution to revolutionize medical logistics, with significant implications for improving efficiency and accessibility in the healthcare sector.",
